SUMMARY:Deadline: SOUND/IMAGE 2026: "Artistic Intelligence" - Call for Work
 s
DESCRIPTION:SOUND/IMAGE 2026 is the 11th edition of the University of Green
 wich festival exploring sound and image practice\, running 5-8 November 20
 26 in London. This year's theme is "Artistic Intelligence": a critical ref
 lection on creative choice\, agency\, and authenticity in the context of a
 lgorithmic and AI-mediated art making. The festival cites reference points
  from Vera Molnár\, Pauline Oliveros\, John Cage\, Iannis Xenakis\, Ryoji
  Ikeda\, and Refik Anadol. Special consideration is given to students\, ap
 prentices\, and emerging artists\; submissions are welcome from composers\
 , filmmakers\, artists\, performers\, and architects. CATEGORIES ACCEPTED:
  sound and music works\; audiovisual works\; talks\; artist statements\; w
 orkshops and practical demonstrations\; live performances\; installations.
  THEMATIC AREAS: embodied knowledge and lived experience in aesthetic judg
 ement\; creative choice vs chance encounters\; ownership\, authenticity\, 
 and AI co-creation\; human and algorithmic capability\; spatial and immers
 ive audio-visual forms\; interdisciplinary practice (CreaTech)\; practice 
 research. SUBMISSION RULES: works under 15 minutes in duration (installati
 ons exempt from duration limit)\; maximum three submissions per artist acr
 oss all categories\; artists must attend and present in person\; submit se
 parately for each submission via Microsoft CMT. FESTIVAL PASS: all accepte
 d artists must purchase a festival pass at a reduced rate of £25. Notific
 ations before end of July 2026. Deadline: 19 June 2026\, 23:59 UTC+1 (exte
 nded from 12 June). Submit at https://blogs.gre.ac.uk/sound-image/sound-im
 age-2026-call-for-works/.\n\nOrganisation: University of Greenwich\nLocati
 on: University of Greenwich\, London\, UK\; in-person attendance required.
 \nAward: No payment to artists. All accepted artists must purchase a festi
 val pass at a reduced rate of £25 (covers catering and technical support)
 .\nDuration: Festival runs 5-8 November 2026.\n\nMore: https://blogs.gre.a
 c.uk/sound-image/sound-image-2026-call-for-works/?utm_source=artificialnou
 veaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
